  "descr_cn": "<p class=\"word-cn\">赫维勒尔温泉是冰岛高地的一个著名温泉区，位于朗格冰川和霍夫斯冰原之间，是冰岛最受欢迎的自然绿洲之一。</p><p class=\"word-en\">Hveravellir is a famous hot spring area in the Icelandic highlands, located between the two major glaciers Langjökull and Hofsjökull, and is one of the most popular natural oases in Iceland.</p><p class=\"word-cn\">这个温泉区以其丰富的地热活动而闻名，包括蒸汽喷泉、泥浆坑和多彩的温泉池，为游客提供了一种独特的自然体验。</p><p class=\"word-en\">This hot spring area is known for its abundant geothermal activities, including steam geysers, mud pits, and colorful hot springs, offering visitors a unique natural experience.</p><p class=\"word-cn\">赫维勒尔温泉的温泉池水温适宜，常年保持在38-40摄氏度之间，是放松身心、享受自然温泉的理想之地。</p><p class=\"word-en\">The temperature of the hot springs in Hveravellir is suitable for bathing, constantly maintained between 38-40 degrees Celsius, making it an ideal place to relax and enjoy natural hot springs.</p><p class=\"word-cn\">除了温泉，赫维勒尔温泉区还提供了多条徒步小径，让游客可以探索周围的熔岩地和山脉，体验冰岛高地的壮丽景色。</p><p class=\"word-en\">In addition to the hot springs, the Hveravellir area also offers several hiking trails, allowing visitors to explore the surrounding lava fields and mountain slopes, experiencing the magnificent scenery of the Icelandic highlands.</p><p class=\"word-cn\">赫维勒尔温泉区的历史可以追溯到19世纪初，当时它是一个重要的交通驿站，为穿越冰岛高地的旅行者提供了休息和补给的场所。</p><p class=\"word-en\">The history of Hveravellir dates back to the early 19th century when it was an important transportation hub, providing a place for travelers crossing the Icelandic highlands to rest and resupply.</p><p class=\"word-cn\">今天，赫维勒尔温泉不仅是一个热门的旅游目的地，也是一个研究地热活动和保护自然生态的重要地点。</p><p class=\"word-en\">Today, Hveravellir is not only a popular tourist destination but also an important site for studying geothermal activities and protecting the natural ecology.</p>",
