  "descr_cn": "<p class=\"word-cn\">死海，这个位于以色列和约旦交界处的神秘之地，是地球上最低的湖泊，也是最咸的湖泊之一。</p><p class=\"word-en\">The Dead Sea, located at the border between Israel and Jordan, is the lowest lake on Earth and one of the saltiest.</p><p class=\"word-cn\">它以其高盐分和独特的矿物质含量而闻名，湖水的盐度是普通海水的8倍多，使得这里成为了一个几乎没有任何生物的‘死’海。</p><p class=\"word-en\">It is famous for its high salinity and unique mineral content, with a salinity eight times that of ordinary seawater, making it an almost lifeless 'dead' sea.</p><p class=\"word-cn\">死海的海水和富含矿物质的泥浆被认为具有治疗皮肤病和其他健康问题的功效，每年吸引着成千上万的游客前来体验。</p><p class=\"word-en\">The waters and mineral-rich mud of the Dead Sea are believed to have therapeutic properties for skin diseases and other health issues, attracting thousands of tourists every year.</p><p class=\"word-cn\">在这里，游客可以体验到在超咸的海水中漂浮的奇妙感觉，同时享受周围沙漠和山丘的壮丽景色。</p><p class=\"word-en\">Here, visitors can experience the unique feeling of floating in the hypersaline water while enjoying the magnificent scenery of the surrounding deserts and hills.</p><p class=\"word-cn\">死海周围地区也是考古学上的重要地点，发现了多处古代遗迹。</p><p class=\"word-en\">The area around the Dead Sea is also an important archaeological site, with many ancient ruins discovered.</p>",
